cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new analog network coding scheme and analyzes its performance in terms of bit error rate. This falls under the scope of information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with bidirectional relay networks and proposes a new scheme for improving their performance. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new scheme for relay networks and analyzes its performance. This falls under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with communication in relay networks and proposes a new scheme for improving their performance. This falls under the scope of communication and networking.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper proposes a new modulation scheme for relay networks and analyzes its performance in terms of bit error rate. This falls under the scope of multimedia.
